To see the list of nodes connected to ansible (The 3 commands works fine)

ansible all --list-hosts

 ansible-inventory --graph --vars

ansible-inventory --list --yaml

To check if they are actually "connected"

ansible all -m ping



TO CHECK CPU AND MEMORY ON ALL NODES 

 ansible all -m setup | grep -i mem

 ansible all -m setup | grep -i cpus

TO CHECK OS TYPE 

ansible all -m setup | grep -i family


TO SCALE UP RAM/CPU FOR A NODE 

Go to aws
Stop the machine
Naviagte > instance settings >  change instance type 
Start instance 

Then you can run the command above to check 
